Sentencas: This work discusses the effect of partial substitution of cobalt in Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) by Mo (VI) cations on the crystal structure, microstructure and transport properties of doped materials.
Titulo: Mixed conducting molybdenum doped BSCF materials

Sentencas: Ba(0.5)Sr(0.5)Co(0.8-x)Mo(x)Fe0(.2)O(3-delta) (BSCFMx) samples possess specific microstructure consisting of double perovskite domains distributed in the cubic perovskite matrix that results in the suppression of undesirable cubic-hexagonal phase transition at x >= 0.02.
Titulo: Mixed conducting molybdenum doped BSCF materials

Sentencas: Doped BSCFMx perovskites demonstrate high oxygen permeability, improved CO2 tolerance, enhanced electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility with Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta electrolyte that allows to consider them as promising candidates both for oxygen transport membranes and cathodes for intermediate temperature SOFC.
Titulo: Mixed conducting molybdenum doped BSCF materials
